                        Mail and Shipping Procedures


                          MAIL ROOM DAILY SCHEDULE:
   By 8:00 a.m. Incoming mail received from USPS. image of mail carrier
   By 10:30 a.m. Mail staff picks up Express mail flats and small boxes
   that were delivered to Shipping & Receiving in Building 22.
   Mail staff picks up mail at USPS.
   Morning Mail Delivery
   10:30-1:30 p.m. Morning Mail sorted for afternoon delivery, including
   Express Mail received that morning.
   Outgoing mail sorted and metered.
   1:00-2:00 p.m. Afternoon Mail Delivery
   by 2:30 p.m. Outgoing mail sorted, metered and taken to USPS.
   By 3:30 p.m. Late arrival Express Mail processed.
   Mass mailings processed.
   Tracking packages,etc.
   Administrative items

                    SHIPPING & RECEIVING DAILY SCHEDULE:
   Morning Most freight received, including Express freight. Most incoming
   freight is scheduled for the next delivery run for DSRC or NIST.
   Shipping & Receiving sorts out flats and small packages for Mail staff
   next delivery.
   All Day: All items security scanned upon arrival.
   Notifications to clients of priority shipments.
   Morning
   Deliveries: NOAA, DSRC and Building 2
   Afternoon
   Deliveries: Building One and all other buildings
   Express
   Freight: Clients are encouraged to notify Shipping/Receiving of
   incoming priority deliveries.Ground and second day air shipments are
   scheduled for the next delivery run. Priority overnight shipments are
   processed as quickly as possible. After shipments are divided into
   ground and overnight, we contact addressees of priority shipments for
   delivery. If waiting for the next scheduled delivery run is a problem,
   clients are permitted to personally pick up shipments at Building 22.
   Every effort possible will be made to deliver overnight freight the
   same day it arrives.
   A signature is required for all deliveries (except mail) and also for
   items picked up at Building 22.
   Special
   Situations: Some items (heavy, large, furniture, etc.) require
   coordination with recipient. Clients should contact Shipping &
   Receiving if a priority delivery is required. Clients may pick up
   freight themselves if they wish.

